The '''Ministry of Environmental Protection and Agriculture of Georgia''' ({{lang-ka|საქართველოს გარემოს დაცვისა და სოფლის მეურნეობის სამინისტრო}}, ''sakartvelos garemos datsvisa da soplis meurneobis saministro'') is a [[governmental agency]] within the [[Cabinet of Georgia]] in charge of regulation of economic activity in the [[Agriculture in Georgia (country)|agricultural sector of the country]] and environment protection with a purpose of increasing the sector's production capacity. The ministry is headed by [[Gigla Agulashvili]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.government.gov.ge/index.php?lang_id=ENG&sec_id=124&mod_id=0&info_id=0&new_year=0&limit=0&date=&new_month=&entrant=2 |title=Government of Georgia |accessdate=2011-03-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928081927/http://www.government.gov.ge/index.php?lang_id=ENG&sec_id=124&mod_id=0&info_id=0&new_year=0&limit=0&date=&new_month=&entrant=2 |archivedate=2011-09-28 |df= }}</ref>
==Structure== The ministry is headed by a minister, first deputy minister and two deputy ministers. It is subdivided into General Inspection, Management Unit for Food Safety and Risk Analysis, Department of Cooperation with International Organizations and Projects Management which overlook divisions on Rural Development, Region Rule, Legal Issues, etc.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.moa.gov.ge/index.php?l=2&pg=str |title=Ministry of Agriculture of Georgia. Structure |accessdate=2011-03-24}}</ref> In December 2017, the [[Ministry of Environment and Natural Resources Protection of Georgia|Ministry of Environment and Natural Resources Protection]] was abolished and merged into that of Agriculture, which was renamed into the Ministry of Environmental Protection and Agriculture of Georgia.<ref>{{cite news|title=New Government Wins Confidence Vote|url=http://civil.ge/eng/article.php?id=30753|accessdate=23 December 2017|work=Civil Georgia|date=22 December 2017}}</ref>
