==World Congress==
The World Congress of the World Federation of the Deaf has been held every four years since 1951. Organised by the WFD and the host country, this event is attended by thousands of Deaf people from all over the world. As well as convening the General Assembly (the highest decision-making body of the WFD) and forming the guidelines for the next four years of its work, the congress holds a large cultural program including theatre performances, cinema, exhibitions, performing arts, visits to local places of interest.<ref>{{cite web|title=World Congress|url=http://wfdeaf.org/about/world-congress|work=World Federation of the Deaf|accessdate=17 August 2013}}</ref>

